ook will be essential reading for scholars and students of Achebe’s work in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / African.2bisacsh  aA Man of the People.  aAchebe, Chinua.  aAnthills of the Savannah.  aArrow of God.  aEnglish Language Literature.  aNigeria.  aNo Longer at Ease.  aThings Fall Apart.1 aMorrison, Jago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611071840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526110718423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526110718/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles